Class ReferenceFilter<BDO extends DataObject,R extends Indexed>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.filter.SQLValueFilter<BDO>

  • Type Parameters:
    BDO - type of factory
    R - indexed type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseFilter<BDO>, BaseSQLFilter<BDO>, PatternFilter<BDO>, SQLFilter<BDO>, Targetted<BDO>

    public final class ReferenceFilter<BDO extends DataObject,R extends Indexed>
extends SQLValueFilter<BDO>
implements SQLFilter<BDO>
    Generic SQL filter for selecting records using a peer Object that implements Indexed referenced from a integer field.

    As DataObject implements Indexed it can used for implementing filters on fields that reference other DataObject tables. In this case it is a good idea to subclass again so as to improve type safety and hide the field name.

    spb
